{
  "stem": "15174.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And it was-- So about an hour after I arrived at this camp, I started to cry, and I cried for a week until they came to pick me up.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "However, you know, the story has a nice side to it because at that camp, I met two guys who were my age who spoke some Yiddish, so we were able to communicate a little.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And those two guys are still two of my best friends today.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "One lives in Boston, one lives in Buffalo, one is a lawyer, one's a doctor.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So-- And then in September I started school.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And by November, I was speaking English fluently.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "What they did was they asked me what grade I was in and I told them I was in fifth grade.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So they put me in fifth grade.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Well, you know, I didn't understand a word the teacher was saying.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I couldn't follow anything.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So they-- the principal decided that she would put me in first grade, and then as I learned a little they would put me in second grade until I worked my way up to the fifth grade again.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "This, by the way, was School 53.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was in the old-- what was called the Humboldt section on the East side.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was a lovely section at that time-- very-- a very Jewish section.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And-- and so by November I was-- I was back in fifth grade, I was speaking English fluently.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I couldn't understand why my parents weren't speaking English fluently.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean I was, why weren't they?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well, of course, I didn't realize that it was much more difficult for adults to learn the language, but they-- they eventually learned it, my mother much better than my father.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then, of course, they spoke with an accent.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
